ity is that the ACTH is elevated due to a tumor elsewhere, like a bronchial carcinoid tumor.","dimension":3,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02636,0.054273,0.074257,0.086881,0.093898,0.09899,0.10308,0.10649,0.10489,0.10417,0.084885,0.061836],"unified_progress":[0.031543,0.065491,0.084056,0.096347,0.099527,0.10047,0.10324,0.10182,0.097938,0.092095,0.075237,0.052235]},{"section":11,"text":"Those can produce ACTH and cause similar symptoms.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030304,0.04749,0.064208,0.076742,0.09259,0.10292,0.10807,0.11297,0.11236,0.09992,0.082973,0.069461],"unified_progress":[0.033286,0.058557,0.079013,0.091835,0.098973,0.10892,0.10783,0.10424,0.098008,0.090369,0.073404,0.055571]},{"section":12,"text":"Also, the presence of hemoptysis might be due to the tumor affecting the bronchial passages.","dimension":1,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042251,0.062998,0.074036,0.083029,0.089652,0.095849,0.10092,0.10238,0.10032,0.094415,0.083732,0.070421],"unified_progress":[0.048192,0.070365,0.082043,0.09065,0.095777,0.098866,0.09793,0.097944,0.094643,0.086457,0.07493,0.062204]},{"section":13,"text":"So putting it together, the elevated ACTH not suppressing with dexamethasone, truncal obesity, hypertension, and smoking history point towards a bronchial carcinoid tumor.","dimension":4,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02432,0.038846,0.047723,0.054377,0.058283,0.063969,0.070254,0.080782,0.092109,0.11205,0.1439,0.21339],"unified_progress":[0.02332,0.037662,0.04648,0.056555,0.060881,0.072104,0.076598,0.087031,0.097566,0.10536,0.14478,0.19166]},{"section":14,"text":"That makes sense because these tumors can cause the release of ACTH, leading to the symptoms mentioned.","dimension":2,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030212,0.039469,0.050329,0.059489,0.070516,0.079681,0.088322,0.098288,0.1075,0.11281,0.11927,0.14411],"unified_progress":[0.027835,0.042263,0.055979,0.